📘 PROJECT EXECUTION PRD
Project Name: AIEcon
Product: AI Feature Unit Economics Simulator
Version: v1 (Simulation-Only)
1️⃣ PRODUCT THESIS (DO NOT DEVIATE)
We help AI SaaS founders model and optimize the unit economics of their AI features before they scale.
The system must answer:
What is my AI cost per user?
What is my gross margin?
What happens at 10k / 100k users?
Which architecture gives better margin?
This is NOT a prompt optimizer.
This is NOT a token calculator.
This is a financial decision simulator.
2️⃣ TECH STACK (MANDATORY)
Backend
Framework: NestJS (TypeScript, strict mode)
ORM: Prisma
Validation: class-validator
Architecture: Modular Monolith
Database
PostgreSQL
JSONB allowed for scenario storage
Frontend
Next.js (App Router)
TypeScript (strict)
TailwindCSS
No Redux / no heavy state managers
React hooks only
Deployment
Frontend: Vercel
Backend: Render
DB: Managed Postgres
Do NOT change stack.
3️⃣ SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
Pattern: Modular Monolith
/apps
  /web
  /api
/packages
  /types
  /utils
  /calculators
/prisma
4️⃣ CORE MODULES
Only 3 modules in v1:
Auth
Scenario Simulator
Architecture Engine
Nothing else.
No Slack.
No Jira.
No SDK.
No tracking.
No billing in v1.
5️⃣ DATABASE MODELS
model User {
  id        String   @id @default(uuid())
  email     String   @unique
  createdAt DateTime @default(now())
  scenarios Scenario[]
}

model Scenario {
  id                 String   @id @default(uuid())
  userId             String
  name               String
  model              String
  avgInputTokens     Int
  avgOutputTokens    Int
  requestsPerUser    Int
  projectedUsers     Int
  subscriptionPrice  Float
  createdAt          DateTime @default(now())
  user               User     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id])
}
No additional tables in v1.
6️⃣ FINANCIAL CALCULATION ENGINE
Create reusable module:
/packages/calculators/unitEconomics.ts
Functions Required
calculatePerRequestCost(model, inputTokens, outputTokens)
Uses internal pricing map:
const MODEL_PRICING = {
  "gpt-4": { input: 0.01, output: 0.03 }, // example per 1k tokens
  "gpt-4-mini": { input: 0.002, output: 0.006 }
}
Return cost per request.
calculateMonthlyCost(perRequestCost, requestsPerUser, projectedUsers)
monthlyCost = perRequestCost × requestsPerUser × projectedUsers
calculateCostPerUser(perRequestCost, requestsPerUser)
costPerUser = perRequestCost × requestsPerUser
calculateGrossMargin(subscriptionPrice, costPerUser)
margin = (subscriptionPrice - costPerUser) / subscriptionPrice
Return percentage.
calculateBreakEven(subscriptionPrice, costPerUser)
breakEvenUsers = fixedCost / (subscriptionPrice - costPerUser)
(Assume fixedCost = 0 in v1, but leave extensible.)
7️⃣ ARCHITECTURE SIMULATION ENGINE
Create:
/packages/calculators/architectureSimulator.ts
It must simulate:
Full GPT-4
GPT-4 Mini
Hybrid fallback (20% GPT-4, 80% Mini)
RAG-style (reduce input tokens by 50%)
Each simulation returns:
{
  architectureName,
  costPerUser,
  monthlyCost,
  grossMargin
}
No AI needed in v1.
Pure deterministic math.
8️⃣ API ENDPOINTS
POST /scenario
Create scenario
GET /scenario/:id
Return scenario + computed results
GET /scenario/:id/simulations
Return architecture comparisons
9️⃣ FRONTEND UX FLOW
Step 1 — Define Feature
Form fields:
Model
Avg input tokens
Avg output tokens
Requests per user per month
Projected active users
SaaS subscription price
Step 2 — Show Financial Output
Display:
Cost per request
Cost per user
Monthly AI cost
Gross margin %
Risk level
Risk rule:
Margin > 75% → Low
50–75% → Medium
< 50% → High
Step 3 — Architecture Comparison Table
Architecture	Cost/User	Margin	Risk
Sorted by highest margin.
🔟 CODING GUIDELINES (STRICT)
SOLID
Controllers: HTTP only
Services: business logic only
Calculators: pure functions only
No DB access inside controllers
DRY
All math logic in /packages/calculators
No duplicated pricing logic
Centralized model pricing config
Type Safety
Strict TypeScript
No any
DTO validation for all API inputs
Dependency Injection
Inject calculator services into modules
No static calls inside controllers
Error Handling
Centralized exception filter
No console.log in production
1️⃣1️⃣ TESTING REQUIREMENTS
Minimum 80% coverage.
Unit Tests
Cost per request
Cost per user
Gross margin
Architecture simulation
Edge cases (zero tokens, zero users)
Integration Tests
Create scenario
Fetch scenario
Fetch simulation
1️⃣2️⃣ PERFORMANCE RULES
All calculations synchronous (fast math only)
No blocking I/O
No external calls in v1
